# Repository Architecture
## fm-subtype-discovery

---

## Folder Structure

```
fm-subtype-discovery/
│
├── README.md                          # Project overview + setup instructions
├── requirements.txt                   # All Python dependencies pinned
├── .gitignore                         # Excludes data/, checkpoints/, __pycache__/
│
├── data/                              # NOT pushed to GitHub -- local only
│   ├── raw/                           # Symlink or pointer to ~/Desktop/DATA
│   ├── clinical/                      # Symlink or pointer to ~/Desktop/DATA_clinical
│   └── README.md                      # Documents where data lives locally
│
├── preprocessing/                     # Eva -- data preparation scripts
│   ├── run_fmriprep.sh                # Docker command to run fMRIPrep
│   ├── extract_roi_timeseries.py      # fMRIPrep output → 200 ROI CSVs per subject
│   ├── compute_fc_matrices.py         # ROI CSVs → 7 FC matrices per subject
│   │                                  #   ⚠ CHANGED: this file must only output FC
│   │                                  #   matrices. The legacy buildSparse graph-writer
│   │                                  #   path (writing _PyGGraph_*.pt with degree/
│   │                                  #   clustering-coefficient/spectral-norm features)
│   │                                  #   is DELETED -- it was orphaned (nothing
│   │                                  #   imported it) and used broken feature defs.
│   │                                  #   Graph construction lives ONLY in
│   │                                  #   models/dataset.py now.
│   │                                  #   Also now includes: framewise displacement
│   │                                  #   computation per condition epoch, motion
│   │                                  #   exclusion (FD>0.5mm in >25% volumes),
│   │                                  #   high-pass filter (0.01Hz cutoff, full run,
│   │                                  #   pre-slicing) -- NO low-pass, see Section 3.2
│   │                                  #   rationale in paper.
│   └── verify_setup.py               # Checks all dependencies installed correctly
│
├── models/                            # Nikhil -- all PyTorch model code
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── dataset.py                     # PyTorch Geometric dataset class
│   │                                  #   CANONICAL graph-construction path: 5 signal
│   │                                  #   node features (mean, variance, 3 FFT bands),
│   │                                  #   global 80th-percentile edge threshold.
│   │                                  #   NEW: getGroupedBySubject() method -- purely
│   │                                  #   additive, does not touch __getitem__/__len__/
│   │                                  #   flat DataList path. Returns
│   │                                  #   {subject_id, graphs: [7 Data], group_label}
│   │                                  #   per subject for joint_train compatibility.
│   │                                  #   Verify against subjectData if already present
│   │                                  #   before treating as new work.
│   ├── gnn_encoder.py                 # 3-layer GATv2 encoder
│   │                                  #   NEW: optional return_attention_weights param
│   │                                  #   on forward(), default False, zero behavior
│   │                                  #   change for existing callers. Exposes final
│   │                                  #   GATv2Conv layer's (edge_index, alpha) for
│   │                                  #   interpretability.py.
│   ├── attention_pool.py              # Condition attention pooling layer, learned τ_attn
│   ├── contrastive_loss.py            # NT-Xent loss (Eva)
│   └── augmentations.py              # Node masking + edge noise (Eva)
│                                      #   Stochastic at training time only -- confirmed
│                                      #   NOT to be baked into saved/preprocessed data,
│                                      #   which would break contrastive view diversity.
│
├── src/                               # Nikhil -- training and clustering
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── train.py                       # Full training loop; joint_train (end-to-end,
│   │                                  #   canonical) + legacy trainer (flat, kept for
│   │                                  #   compatibility)
│   ├── hyperparameter_search.py       # Optuna hyperparameter search
│   │                                  #   ⚠ RESCOPED from Ray Tune ASHA: single-GPU,
│   │                                  #   minutes-long runs make ASHA's early-kill value
│   │                                  #   negligible and adds multiprocessing complexity
│   │                                  #   for no scientific payoff. Optuna/random search
│   │                                  #   over {d_model, heads, layers, dropout, lr}
│   │                                  #   produces the same Section 4.5 table.
│   ├── clustering.py                  # Extract embeddings + k-means
│   │                                  #   NEW: perm() and gap_stat() from evaluate.py
│   │                                  #   wired in -- FM-vs-HC separation, FM-only
│   │                                  #   clustering, and orthogonal-projected
│   │                                  #   clustering all now carry permutation
│   │                                  #   p-values; gap statistic reported alongside
│   │                                  #   silhouette in k-selection.
│   │                                  #   Confirmed: centroid-to-HC distance computed
│   │                                  #   in same space (projected/unprojected) as the
│   │                                  #   corresponding clustering result.
│   │                                  #   Confirmed: condition order matches events.tsv
│   │                                  #   confirmed order (see below).
│   └── ablations.py                   # 4 ablations, confirmed scope:
│                                      #   run_no_pretraining, run_resting_state,
│                                      #   run_no_pooling, run_mean_pooling.
│                                      #   run_3feature_nodes and run_identity_features
│                                      #   CUT -- redundant given settled node-feature
│                                      #   scheme, no paper claim needs them.
│
├── analysis/                          # Eva -- evaluation and clinical validation
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── clinical_validation.py         # Mann-Whitney U + FDR + Cohen's d
│   │                                  #   NEW: post-hoc power analysis
│   │                                  #   (statsmodels.stats.power), framed as
│   │                                  #   prospective sample-size-for-future-study,
│   │                                  #   not observed/post-hoc power.
│   ├── evaluate.py                    # Silhouette + permutation test (perm) +
│   │                                  #   gap statistic (gap_stat) -- implemented,
│   │                                  #   now actually called from clustering.py
│   ├── interpretability.py            # GAT attention weight extraction + brain maps
│   │                                  #   3-tuple unpack fix, entropy, τ_attn: DONE.
│   │                                  #   NEW: Yeo-Krienen 7-network mapping
│   │                                  #   (Schaefer-200 → Yeo-7 lookup, per-network
│   │                                  #   attention aggregation per subtype).
│   │                                  #   Per-region attention extraction depends on
